data.title: Minneapolis StarTribune
data.meta_description: Minneapolis StarTribune - a place for remembering loved ones; a space for sharing memories, life stories, milestones, to express condolences, and celebrate life of your loved ones
data.text:
Wayne Allen

Allen, Wayne C. age 90, of Howard Lake passed away on 7/28/24. He served in the US Navy from 1953- 1956. He worked at Honeywell Aerospace in Mpls, and retired from FMC/BAE in 1992. Wayne was active in BSA Troop 206 and Trinity Lutheran Church, Long Lake. He enjoyed time with family, camping, hunting and...

Margaret Anderson

Margaret 'Peggy' Anderson, born August 24th, 1939, passed away July 23rd, 2024 at the age of 84, three years and two days after her beloved John. We all know that she must've wanted her own day and she got it. Peggy was the sweetest ball of fire you'd ever meet. While her bright light may have left this Earth, we...

Mary Andrew

Mary died on June 22, 2024 from complications of diabetes. Preceded in death by infant daughter, Emily, and parents, Charles and Grace. Mary is survived by her son, Paul Anderson; grandchildren, Natallya "Tally" Anderson and Tyler Anderson; siblings, Michael (Jeanne Pickering), Mark (Connie), Maureen (Jay Hanson),...

Robert Bakke

Bakke, Robert "Bob" Wessel 87, passed away on July 27, 2024 in Bloomington, MN. Son of Hanna Wessel Bakke (Klausen), and Olaf Jacob Severin Bakke, he was born February 22, 1937 in Brooklyn, NY. Bob graduated from Minnehaha Academy (1955) and Wheaton College (1959) where he studied Business. Bob was chosen 1st team...

John Bartle

Bartle, John Paul Passed away suddenly at his home in Dayton. A Memorial Gathering for John will be Friday, August 23rd from 3-6PM at Hidden Haven Golf Club, 20520 Polk Street NE, Cedar, MN. In lieu of flowers, memorials preferred to family. Memorials will be distributed to agencies who have helped with John's cats...

Anne Bartz

Bartz, Anne Louise Age 73, of St. Paul, passed away peacefully on August 6, 2024. Preceded in death by parents, Harlow and Magel Boyd; brother Lee Boyd; and brother-in-law, Leon Hovland. She will be sadly missed by husband, Sherman; sister, Mary Hovland; many nieces, nephews, great-nieces, great-nephews, and...

Jan Boylan

Four years and still deeply missed "so much bad." Until we meet again mama, may you sing with the angels and continue to feel our love

Jill & Kelly

KEN "KENNY" CZUPTA

KEN "KENNY" CZUPTA Aug. 5, 1968 Aug. 20, 2006 Hi Ken, Tomorrow would be your 56th Birthday, August 5, 1968. You were actually born on a Monday. Wishing you a very Happy Birthday. Love, Love, Love You! Mom, David, Cindy, Family & Friends

Adam Engman-Delforge

Adam Engman-Delforge 8/4/80 - 3/28/03 "If I could turn back time, If I could find a way, If I could reach the stars, I'd give 'em all to you." I remember you every day, but especially on your birthday. Love you forever, Your Mother

Brian Toivonen

Brian Toivonen Happy Birthday! Love Always, Mom XOXO "May you see the reflection of your life's kindness and beauty in all the tears that fall for you." Send a kid skiing - http://Give.RidingOnInsulin.org/brian

Joy Whipps

In Memory of Joy Whipps 10/7/46 - 7/31/04 It's been 20 years since you left us. Time has gone so fast but our love has not. We will always love you. Love, Bob and best friend Patricia.

Raymond B. Anthony

Raymond B. Anthony March 11, 1952 - July 29, 2022 My little brother and best friend. I miss our weekly phone calls when we discussed every topic under the sun. I miss your willingness to always help others and how you always looked out for me. You will always be in our hearts.
